  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-Sectoral and Integrated Humanitarian and Recovery Support for South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using an integrated and multi-sectoral approach encompassing activities in displacement tracking, camp coordination and camp management, shelter and non-food items, water, sanitation and hygiene, health, mental health and psychosocial support, protection, common pipeline, and the Common Transport Service, IOM seeks to ensure effective and timely delivery of humanitarian and recovery assistance for affected populations in South Sudan. IOM&#x2019;s efforts will focus upon three interlinked and mutually reinforcing areas of intervention: camps and camp-like settings; underserved and hard-to-reach areas facing great severity of humanitarian needs; and humanitarian coordination. IOM will promote the involvement of a wide range of actors and encourage complementarity between humanitarian partners and clusters to make programming more cost-effective, reach a greater portion of the affected population and better respond to new protection concerns.</narrative>
  </description>
